  "texts": [
    "More than 1/3 works directly adapted existing pre-trained models to their tasks in language, and multimodal fields, excepting the bioinformatics.",
    "The vision and language in healthcare and general fields are relatively unified compared with the bioinformatics, thus some successful pre-trained models in the general field also will be generalized to healthcare tasks.",
    "Bioinformatics lacks general pre-trained models for their very specific omics data, so that only two works [212], [213] studied the direct adaptation of the embedding from LFMs.2) Most LFMs directly adapted existing pre-trained language models to their healthcare tasks.",
    "Because language, as the data created by human beings, has strong portability.",
    "The LFM pre-trained in general field has this portability and are able to adapt to the healthcare field.3) Most pre-training works focused on learning without annotations."
